FBIS3-7722 "dreeu039_k_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 CROATIA Protest Made to Slovenia Over Piran Bay LD2502192694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 25 Feb 94 LD2502192694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Croatian Deputy Foreign Minister Ivo Sanader today delivered a protest note to Andrej Zlebnik, charge d'affaires at the Slovene Embassy in Zagreb, in the absence of Slovene Ambassador Malesic. The note refers to frequent incidents involving Slovene police in Croatian territorial waters in Piran Bay. The note says that such incidents preempt a final solution of the border problem in Piran Bay, which is being addressed by a joint Croatian-Slovene diplomatic border commission. Deputy Minister Sanader says that Croatia is interested in maintaining good neighborly relations with Slovenia and solving all open issues by mutual agreement.
